00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:44.000
and the things that don't work in Spark

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:47.000
and the things that don't work properly in sparklyr, et cetera.

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:51.000
So the idea now is if you guys are interested, I'll have some links at the end,

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:55.000
you can go in and you can get yourself comfortable with R connecting to Spark

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:59.000
and leveraging the power of Spark without having to give up on R.

